The paper deals with the problem of finding a representative subset of a large collection of data points or models, which is a common problem in many areas of computer science such as computer vision (cs.CV), recommender systems (cs.IR), and natural language processing (cs.CL). The proposed formulation involves row-sparsity regularized trace minimization, which is a common technique in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of dissimilarities between elements, which is a common approach in data science and clustering (cs.DS). Finally, the paper presents experiments on real-world datasets, which is a common practice in many areas of computer science (cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.CL).
